<TITLE> 11 highway police removed from post on extortion charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)  All 11 police personnel, including two sergeants, of a highway police post in Sirajganj district were removed from duty on Monday, as charges of extortion and other irregularities mounted against them, an official said. "The measure has been taken against the officers, stationed at Kadda police post on the west side Bangabandhu Bridge, as we received different allegations against them, including extortion, from drivers of the area," Siranjganj police chief Md Mosharaf Hossain told bdnews24.com. He said all 11 were sent back to police lines. The two sergeants have been identified as Mofakkharul Islam and Belal Hossain. bdn
